(a) A person under the age of eighteen who holds a permit may renew the permit by paying a three-dollar fee.
The department shall credit the fee to the highway safety fund.
(b) An agricultural driving permit is invalidated when a permittee attains age eighteen.
In order to drive a motor vehicle on a highway he or she must obtain a motor vehicle driver's license under this chapter.
(4) Suspension, revocation, or cancellation.
The director has sole discretion to suspend, revoke, or cancel a juvenile agricultural driving permit if: (a) The permittee has been convicted of an offense that requires mandatory suspension or revocation of a driver's license; or (b) The director is satisfied that the permittee has violated the permit's restrictions.
